result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron Marques Kendrick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Aaron Marques Kendrick is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Aaron Marques Kendrick was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Aaron Marques Kendrick in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Matter was set for jury trial today.  State is unable to proceed on counts 1, 2, 3, 4 as the victim is not present.    Defense motion to dismiss those counts is granted by the Court without prejudice.
On motion of the State, Court ordered count 5  amended to DISORDERLY CONDUCT, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1), a Class B misdemeanor.
To the amended charge in count 5:   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court by state, defense and defendant.   The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 24 days in the House of Correction, with credit for 24 days time served.  
The court orders defendant to pay all costs, assessments, fees and surcharges, provide DNA and pay costs.  CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT to be applied and any balance due and owing is due by 1-28-2016 or a civil judgment shall be entered.
